## Question 2

@question A premium bakery specializes in artisanal cupcakes and operates with a complex pricing structure. The bakery sells cupcakes in luxury boxes containing exactly 24 cupcakes each. Each luxury box is priced at $18.90 to customers. The bakery's cost analysis shows that each individual cupcake costs $0.42 to produce (including ingredients, labor, and overhead). The bakery aims to maintain a gross profit margin of 35% on each box sold. However, when customers purchase individual cupcakes (not in boxes), the bakery applies a premium pricing strategy with a 65% markup over the effective per-cupcake cost basis used in box pricing. Additionally, the bakery offers a loyalty program where members receive a 12% discount on individual cupcakes. Calculate the final price a loyalty program member would pay for a single cupcake, and determine how much additional profit the bakery makes per cupcake when selling individually to non-members versus selling in boxes.

@instruction Solve this multi-step problem involving percentages, profit margins, markup calculations, and discount applications. Show all intermediate calculations and clearly state your assumptions.
@difficulty hard
